WEBVTT

00:01.543 --> 00:03.420
♪ ♪

00:06.673 --> 00:08.509
(alarm beeping steadily)

00:17.392 --> 00:18.477
AUTOMATED VOICE:
Disarmed.

00:21.355 --> 00:23.774
(Samantha gasps)

00:23.774 --> 00:26.860
-Oh my God!
-Hello, Samantha.

00:26.860 --> 00:28.946
Why are you awake?
It's, like, 4:00 a. m.

00:28.946 --> 00:31.406
For some reason,
I just could not sleep.

00:31.406 --> 00:34.952
Okay, well, I have to be up
pretty early, so I'm gonna...

00:34.952 --> 00:37.204
Right.
Did you have fun with Alex?

00:37.204 --> 00:38.872
-Yeah.
-Nice.

00:38.872 --> 00:40.582
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

00:40.582 --> 00:41.625
Can we talk about it later?

00:41.625 --> 00:43.752
Of course. Please.

00:43.752 --> 00:45.003
Cool.

00:46.463 --> 00:49.591
So, you see, I am not,
in fact, intrusive and nosey.

00:51.510 --> 00:52.803
What is happening right now?

00:52.803 --> 00:54.471
CAROL:
Nothing is happening.

00:54.471 --> 00:57.349
I just don't want to be
overbearing,

00:57.349 --> 00:59.059
and yet absent.

01:02.020 --> 01:04.147
♪ ♪

01:16.785 --> 01:19.329
CAROL:
No, no, don't bother.

01:19.329 --> 01:21.248
Your diary is right here.

01:21.248 --> 01:23.250
That is not my diary,
that is my fourth step.

01:23.250 --> 01:25.669
-Your what?
-It's part of the program, okay?

01:25.669 --> 01:27.337
I-I write out my resentments

01:27.337 --> 01:29.214
and then I let them go.
Give it back to me.

01:29.214 --> 01:32.676
"Selfish, bad behavior,
bad listener.

01:32.676 --> 01:34.636
-Mom.
-This one. "I am resentful

01:34.636 --> 01:36.346
of my mother for her beauty."

01:36.346 --> 01:37.723
Really?

01:37.723 --> 01:38.890
What am I supposed
to do with that?

01:38.890 --> 01:41.268
Nothing!
You don't do anything with that.

01:41.268 --> 01:43.395
"A self-involved narcissist

01:43.395 --> 01:46.273
who tries to cover up
her failures with gardening."

01:46.273 --> 01:48.984
Really, what are my
so-called failures, Samantha?

01:48.984 --> 01:51.445
I am not having
this conversation with you.

01:51.445 --> 01:54.364
Taking that was a huge violation
of my privacy.

01:54.364 --> 01:55.532
-Your privacy.
-Yes.

01:55.532 --> 01:57.576
I am sure everyone

01:57.576 --> 02:00.287
in all of your meetings
knows exactly what's in here.

02:00.287 --> 02:02.331
No, they don't.
Only my sponsor does.

02:02.331 --> 02:06.376
Olivia Elliot of NPR
knows our dirty laundry.

02:06.376 --> 02:08.545
That's wonder-- Shouldn't this
be for your eyes only?

02:08.545 --> 02:09.588
Yes!

02:11.757 --> 02:13.884
Now you know all of it, though.
Are you happy?

02:13.884 --> 02:16.637
-No, it's awful.
-Hey, w-what's going on?

02:16.637 --> 02:18.221
It's like 4:00 in the morning.

02:18.221 --> 02:19.723
Oh, God, why are you
wearing her robe?

02:19.723 --> 02:21.725
Sorry, it's a medical condition.

02:21.725 --> 02:22.851
I don't want to hear
anything else.

02:22.851 --> 02:24.603
It's like a night sweat thing.

02:24.603 --> 02:26.605
I thought she knew
about my sweat thing.

02:26.605 --> 02:27.564
It's really--
It's enough.

02:30.233 --> 02:31.568
Brit.

02:31.568 --> 02:33.654
Okay, let me start by saying

02:33.654 --> 02:35.947
I am not coming to you because
Samantha's otherwise occupied.

02:35.947 --> 02:38.492
Okay, wow, I didn't think
that before, but now I do.

02:38.492 --> 02:40.243
I just really need someone
to complain to.

02:40.243 --> 02:41.578
Fun!
Well, at least I'm not busy

02:41.578 --> 02:43.205
-doing anything.
-Okay, come on, Brit.

02:43.205 --> 02:44.247
You got three minutes, right?

02:44.247 --> 02:46.708
Zacky's dad wants to see me.

02:46.708 --> 02:48.752
Whoa. Trent's in town?

02:48.752 --> 02:51.755
I haven't seen him
since that viral video of him

02:51.755 --> 02:53.674
skateboarding into a dumpster
full of teddy bears.

02:55.008 --> 02:56.218
How is that guy?

02:56.218 --> 02:58.136
He wants to hang out.
Like, alone.

02:58.136 --> 03:00.263
He wants to "talk."

03:00.263 --> 03:01.765
I don't want to talk to him.

03:01.765 --> 03:03.558
I don't have to do this, right?

03:03.558 --> 03:05.477
I mean, he is the father
of your child.

03:05.477 --> 03:07.270
He was.

03:07.270 --> 03:08.522
Before he went and ditched us
to go live his dreams

03:08.522 --> 03:09.856
jumping in dumpsters in L. A.

03:09.856 --> 03:12.275
-Look, I think you got to go.
-Ugh.

03:12.275 --> 03:13.694
I feel like Sam would have
said the same,

03:13.694 --> 03:15.570
but I would have done
the opposite, because... Sam.

03:19.324 --> 03:21.076
(sighs deeply)

03:36.258 --> 03:38.468
(sighs)

03:44.224 --> 03:45.392
-Samantha?
-Oh!

03:46.518 --> 03:47.894
Mindy?

03:47.894 --> 03:50.480
So, uh, what are you doing here?

03:50.480 --> 03:51.773
I'm housesitting
Olivia's plants.

03:51.773 --> 03:53.942
-They were dying from neglect.
-Oh.

03:53.942 --> 03:56.319
It's a dry run to get her
to appoint me godmother.

03:56.319 --> 03:57.612
Godmother?
I thought you hated babies.

03:57.612 --> 03:59.698
Yeah.
The way they can't support

03:59.698 --> 04:02.284
their own heads freaks me out.

04:02.284 --> 04:03.702
What are you doing here?

04:03.702 --> 04:06.329
I don't know, I just felt
like I needed a walk,

04:06.329 --> 04:09.207
and then my feet
kind of took me here.

04:09.207 --> 04:10.625
You want to talk about it?

04:12.335 --> 04:14.796
Olivia's not coming back
for a while, Sam.

04:14.796 --> 04:16.882
-I know.
-I mean, we can

04:16.882 --> 04:18.175
Weekend at Bernie's this
all you want,

04:18.175 --> 04:19.843
but, spoiler alert,
Bernie's dead,

04:19.843 --> 04:21.303
and you need to find
a new sponsor.

04:25.557 --> 04:27.434
(indistinct chatter)

04:32.314 --> 04:33.940
(sighs)

04:33.940 --> 04:36.693
Fink, my office, please.
Chop-chop.

04:40.322 --> 04:42.699
-Hey.
-The Sphinx.

04:42.699 --> 04:44.451
-What?
-New nickname.

04:44.451 --> 04:46.620
Sam, Fink, "Sphinx."

04:46.620 --> 04:48.580
-Sick.
-It's good, right?

04:48.580 --> 04:49.706
-Mm. What do you need?
-So, listen, we got

04:49.706 --> 04:51.583
the New York meeting coming up.

04:51.583 --> 04:52.793
I really want to have
some great ideas,

04:52.793 --> 04:54.252
I need everyone focused.

04:54.252 --> 04:55.754
I really want
to impress Corporate.

04:55.754 --> 04:57.589
I want to show them
how we're gonna take

04:57.589 --> 05:00.675
this dying print publication,
rip it from its grave,

05:00.675 --> 05:01.802
bring it to the future.

05:01.802 --> 05:03.512
Yeah, okay, great.

05:03.512 --> 05:05.096
Let me, uh, think of some stuff.
I'll get back to you.

05:05.096 --> 05:06.139
Here's what I'm thinking.

05:06.139 --> 05:07.516
Stuff like Backpage,

05:07.516 --> 05:09.893
but without the murders, okay?

05:09.893 --> 05:12.312
Maybe we do a podcast,
maybe a TikTok challenge.

05:12.312 --> 05:14.439
-You're Gen Z, right?
-Millennial.

05:14.439 --> 05:16.942
Oh, you're useless to me.
Why are we even...

05:16.942 --> 05:19.277
Hey, Jeff?
Jeff, come here for a sec.

05:19.277 --> 05:21.696
What are you,
generationally speaking?

05:21.696 --> 05:23.657
I'm technically on the cusp.

05:23.657 --> 05:25.867
"On the cusp."
That's an annoying answer.

05:25.867 --> 05:28.995
That's exactly the kind
of Gen Z bullshit I want.

05:28.995 --> 05:31.414
Fink, take a page out of
the Jeff playbook, please.

05:31.414 --> 05:33.750
Jeff, let's do a column

05:33.750 --> 05:36.253
called "On the Cusp With Jeff."

05:36.253 --> 05:38.380
Sam, you have a visitor.
Or it might be a stalker.

05:38.380 --> 05:39.464
-I can't tell.
-Okay, thanks.

05:43.552 --> 05:46.304
(indistinct chatter)

05:46.304 --> 05:49.140
-Bob?
-Sam, hey!

05:49.140 --> 05:50.308
Sorry to barge in.

05:50.308 --> 05:52.602
Boy, this is it, huh?

05:52.602 --> 05:54.187
I mean, I really miss the hubbub
of an office, you know?

05:54.187 --> 05:55.480
-It's just like...
-Yeah.

05:55.480 --> 05:57.023
So fun. Listen, I don't have

05:57.023 --> 05:58.525
a lot of time right now.
Can I help you with something?

05:58.525 --> 05:59.860
No, I-I'm just here

05:59.860 --> 06:02.362
to see how
the sausage gets made.

06:02.362 --> 06:06.324
Okay, so I heard
some of what you guys

06:06.324 --> 06:07.909
-were talking about last night.
-Mm-hmm.

06:07.909 --> 06:10.412
And your mom, she's not feeling
great about what happened.

06:10.412 --> 06:13.832
-Bob.
-Look, if you just
sat down with her,

06:13.832 --> 06:17.210
I think you might be able
to get an apology.

06:17.210 --> 06:19.212
Sorry, you think I'm gonna get
an apology from the woman

06:19.212 --> 06:20.881
who said, "Why did you put
your finger there?"

06:20.881 --> 06:23.300
when she slammed it
in a car door?

06:23.300 --> 06:25.218
Yeah, just sort of flickers.

06:25.218 --> 06:26.469
-Yeah, that's nerve damage.
-Yeah.

06:26.469 --> 06:27.762
BOB:
Ow.

06:27.762 --> 06:29.180
All right,
I can't guarantee anything,

06:29.180 --> 06:30.640
but I know your mom,

06:30.640 --> 06:32.767
and she loves you.

06:32.767 --> 06:35.312
And why not give her a shot
to see if she can

06:35.312 --> 06:36.938
make it right, you know?
What do you have to lose?

06:36.938 --> 06:39.608
What if we do a collab
with Yung Gravy?

06:39.608 --> 06:40.942
-Who?
-The rapper.

06:40.942 --> 06:42.736
Yung Gravy?
Oh, that sounds good.

06:42.736 --> 06:44.779
You hear that, Fink?
This guy's two for two.

06:44.779 --> 06:46.239
-Oh, hey, man.
-Hey.

06:46.239 --> 06:47.490
-How are you?
-I'm good!

06:47.490 --> 06:49.451
-Love that shirt.
-Oh, thank you, love yours.

06:49.451 --> 06:50.577
-That's great.
-That's a fun top.

06:50.577 --> 06:51.911
(chuckling):
Yeah, see?

06:51.911 --> 06:53.663
I love watching
the sausage getting made.

06:53.663 --> 06:54.998
Yeah, hang out, have fun.
I'll see you later.

06:54.998 --> 06:56.458
Oh, good, okay, thanks.
I will, I will.

06:56.458 --> 06:59.210
You're gonna love
this hair oil.

06:59.210 --> 07:00.670
Got it from my girl,
she lives in Hawaii.

07:00.670 --> 07:02.172
(knocking)

07:06.843 --> 07:09.846
Okay, all right.
Looks great.

07:09.846 --> 07:12.474
-(chuckles weakly)
-CLIENT: Thank you.

07:12.474 --> 07:14.684
'Lecia, look at you.

07:14.684 --> 07:16.645
A goddess in her queendom.

07:16.645 --> 07:18.563
My place of employment?
Really?

07:18.563 --> 07:21.566
The perfect place for us to have
a deeply personal conversation.

07:21.566 --> 07:22.817
I mean, I could take you
around the corner

07:22.817 --> 07:24.486
to get a lemon poppyseed muffin.

07:24.486 --> 07:25.820
No. How did you remember
that's my favorite?

07:25.820 --> 07:27.739
Wait, what's your game?
What are you doing here?

07:27.739 --> 07:29.658
What, you like, need money?

07:29.658 --> 07:30.533
Since when have
I ever asked you for money?

07:30.533 --> 07:31.701
So, what do you want?

07:31.701 --> 07:33.453
Trying to get back
in my pants again?

07:33.453 --> 07:34.913
That's not why I'm here.

07:34.913 --> 07:36.706
(sighs)
Look, I'm giving up

07:36.706 --> 07:38.458
-the whole stuntman life.
-(scoffs)

07:38.458 --> 07:40.460
You love doing backflips
off motorcycles,

07:40.460 --> 07:42.253
it's like your favorite thing
in the world.

07:42.253 --> 07:43.797
-Why are you really here?
-I just said it.

07:43.797 --> 07:45.882
I'm done, I'm out. I'm old.

07:45.882 --> 07:48.426
-Dude, you're 28.
-That's my point.

07:48.426 --> 07:49.803
That's, like,
85 in stuntman years.

07:49.803 --> 07:52.806
And this last stunt, I mean,
it really took me out.

07:52.806 --> 07:54.599
But me going through that wall,

07:54.599 --> 07:56.184
it was the best thing
that ever happened to me.

07:56.184 --> 07:57.811
Yeah, I ended up
in this hospital

07:57.811 --> 08:00.480
with this old dude who blasts
Michael Bublé.

08:00.480 --> 08:02.315
And at first, I was like,
yo, this sucks,

08:02.315 --> 08:03.608
fake-ass Sinatra.

08:03.608 --> 08:06.736
But then, he put on
this song called "Home."

08:06.736 --> 08:08.905
You know what it got me
thinking about?

08:08.905 --> 08:11.866
-Let me guess-- home?
-Yes.

08:11.866 --> 08:14.661
But I realized that
when I think about home,

08:14.661 --> 08:16.454
I think about Zacky.

08:17.622 --> 08:21.209
Well, Zack and I
have been at home

08:21.209 --> 08:22.794
without you for a long time,

08:22.794 --> 08:25.797
and, um...
we're doing just fine.

08:25.797 --> 08:28.591
I know, and I'm not trying
to crowd you.

08:28.591 --> 08:30.719
I'd just...

08:30.719 --> 08:32.345
like the chance
to be a part of it.

08:33.471 --> 08:34.681
I'm moving back.

08:34.681 --> 08:36.516
-You are?
-Yeah, yeah.

08:36.516 --> 08:38.893
I got an apartment in Everett
and everything.

08:38.893 --> 08:42.313
I just would love
to see you all more.

08:42.313 --> 08:44.733
Okay, that's--
that's a lot to lay on me

08:44.733 --> 08:46.317
right before I gotta fix a perm.

08:57.203 --> 08:59.914
No needs to feel awkward
about the silence.

08:59.914 --> 09:03.460
Silence allows us to reflect,

09:03.460 --> 09:05.420
to go within.

09:13.636 --> 09:16.181
I also don't want
to oversell the silence,

09:16.181 --> 09:17.807
'cause this feels like
it's a little long now.

09:17.807 --> 09:19.768
-Yeah, I'll start.
-Okay.

09:19.768 --> 09:21.186
I would like to submit

09:21.186 --> 09:23.605
that I skipped
my lunch break for this,

09:23.605 --> 09:25.774
and she still has not
apologized.

09:25.774 --> 09:28.401
Apologize for what?
For what?

09:28.401 --> 09:31.863
You have not explained what all
of my so-called failures are.

09:31.863 --> 09:35.658
Well, I shouldn't have to,
should I?

09:35.658 --> 09:36.826
'Cause those were
my private thoughts.

09:36.826 --> 09:38.411
That's not admissible.

09:38.411 --> 09:40.205
Oh, this is not a court of law,
I'm not really...

09:40.205 --> 09:42.415
Did I fail
when I bought a new car

09:42.415 --> 09:44.626
at an exorbitant rate

09:44.626 --> 09:46.503
because you totaled
my beloved Volvo?

09:46.503 --> 09:50.507
Did I fail when I forked over
40 grand for your rehab?

09:50.507 --> 09:52.967
Did I fail
when I let you off the hook

09:52.967 --> 09:55.678
after you didn't come home
when your father was sick?

09:55.678 --> 09:57.388
-(laughs)
-No, no, no. No.

09:57.388 --> 09:59.474
Those things are not
in your little book

09:59.474 --> 10:01.392
of "reasons I'm mad."

10:01.392 --> 10:02.560
Right, so I don't know
if you know

10:02.560 --> 10:04.395
what the term
"off the hook" means,

10:04.395 --> 10:06.439
'cause you're still
talking about it.

10:06.439 --> 10:08.274
My question has not
been answered.

10:08.274 --> 10:12.362
What did I do
to deserve such vitriol?

10:12.362 --> 10:17.367
Because I am not responsible
for your alcoholism, Samantha.

10:17.367 --> 10:19.202
Well, if you still see me

10:19.202 --> 10:21.704
as that drunk
from two years ago,

10:21.704 --> 10:23.456
then there's nothing to discuss.

10:27.794 --> 10:30.130
BOB:
Well, that was a good start.

10:31.798 --> 10:34.217
Okay, yeah,
Zack loves his dad.

10:34.217 --> 10:35.844
I mean, he's psyched
when Trent rolls into town

10:35.844 --> 10:37.595
and takes him to a movie
where someone

10:37.595 --> 10:40.890
gets their head chopped off,
and feeds him 14 Creamsicles.

10:40.890 --> 10:42.350
But what happens when he gets
another Mountain Dew commercial

10:42.350 --> 10:44.185
and leaves again?

10:44.185 --> 10:46.354
What happens if he doesn't?

10:46.354 --> 10:47.772
-Pete, we have sex.
-Yeah.

10:47.772 --> 10:49.274
So you're supposed to be
on my side automatically.

10:49.274 --> 10:51.693
No, no, no, I am. I am.
(chuckles)

10:51.693 --> 10:53.111
I just, um...

10:54.779 --> 10:57.323
Is there a chance that this
is good for you and Zacky?

10:57.323 --> 10:59.617
Don't do that.

10:59.617 --> 11:02.537
Don't act like
you're all deep and shit,

11:02.537 --> 11:03.788
and got all the answers.

11:03.788 --> 11:05.206
You don't know him
like I know him.

11:05.206 --> 11:06.499
No, I-I don't.

11:06.499 --> 11:08.459
And-and I don't want to be
an asshole here,

11:08.459 --> 11:10.003
but... (sighs)

11:12.172 --> 11:13.381
What if he's changed?

11:14.757 --> 11:17.177
You and Trent were like,
what, 19?

11:17.177 --> 11:18.678
I mean, you were just kids.

11:18.678 --> 11:20.263
FELICIA:
Yep.

11:20.263 --> 11:21.848
And I was the kid
who got stuck with a kid,

11:21.848 --> 11:23.600
and he was the kid who got to do
whatever he wanted.

11:25.268 --> 11:26.811
Hmm.

11:26.811 --> 11:29.355
Look, if Trent wants to spend
more time with Zacky,

11:29.355 --> 11:30.398
I think that's great.

11:32.275 --> 11:33.902
But I'll believe it
when I see it.

11:33.902 --> 11:35.695
I hope you get to see it.

11:37.822 --> 11:39.365
Why don't you give him a shot?

11:39.365 --> 11:42.452
Let him babysit,
and you and I can go out

11:42.452 --> 11:43.703
for a little night
on the town.

11:43.703 --> 11:45.246
Will there be steak?

11:45.246 --> 11:46.539
-You want steak?
-Yeah.

11:46.539 --> 11:47.749
Then there'll be steak.

11:50.251 --> 11:52.170
Sam, this stuff is great,

11:52.170 --> 11:53.630
it's gonna be perfect
for New York.

11:53.630 --> 11:54.923
I do want to change
a couple things, if you can...

11:54.923 --> 11:56.466
Cool, yeah,
I'll get to that later.

11:56.466 --> 11:58.218
(sniffling)

11:58.218 --> 12:00.345
What the hell, are...
you crying?

12:00.345 --> 12:02.639
No.
God, I'm just tired.

12:02.639 --> 12:04.265
Sam, no, no.
Sam, Sam, Sam.

12:04.265 --> 12:05.808
Listen to me for one second.

12:05.808 --> 12:08.478
As your mentor,
I want to just let you know

12:08.478 --> 12:10.813
that you cannot cry at work.

12:10.813 --> 12:13.316
You basically cried to me
last week.

12:13.316 --> 12:15.485
It's a double standard,
I'm aware of that.

12:15.485 --> 12:18.488
But when a man cries at work,

12:18.488 --> 12:22.825
it is essentially him, like,
shedding his toxic masculinity,

12:22.825 --> 12:25.203
and it's a show
of emotional strength.

12:25.203 --> 12:26.496
- And you know...
-No, it's not.

12:26.496 --> 12:27.830
Let's face it,
we both know that women

12:27.830 --> 12:29.540
just get hammered.

12:29.540 --> 12:32.210
They're emotional,
they're hysterical, and just...

12:32.210 --> 12:33.670
Okay, I'm going for a walk.

12:33.670 --> 12:36.130
Yeah, I know, Sam,
it is funny how allergies

12:36.130 --> 12:38.216
look like crying.
Get some Claritin.

12:38.216 --> 12:40.510
All right, guys, keep it up.
Great job.

12:40.510 --> 12:42.637
I'm heading
to New York soon, so...

12:42.637 --> 12:45.181
♪ ♪

12:50.103 --> 12:53.648
♪ I ran into you ♪

12:53.648 --> 12:57.527
