13:48.828 --> 13:52.248
♪ I'm just fine ♪

13:55.793 --> 13:58.671
♪ I'm just fine ♪

14:02.633 --> 14:05.219
♪ I'm just fine ♪

14:15.271 --> 14:16.981
Hey.

14:16.981 --> 14:19.942
Remember when I was 16
and my dad was sick,

14:19.942 --> 14:21.986
and you said
if I ever needed anything...

14:24.697 --> 14:26.074
Yeah. Come on.

14:38.503 --> 14:39.670
OLIVIA:
Carol? Is everything okay?

14:39.670 --> 14:41.380
-Is Sam okay? Did she drink?
-No, no.

14:41.380 --> 14:43.216
It's much worse.

14:43.216 --> 14:45.718
She wrote 50 pages
of horrible things about me

14:45.718 --> 14:47.720
because of your program.

14:47.720 --> 14:52.100
And when I tried to discuss it
with her, she left.

14:52.100 --> 14:53.851
And then you called me.

14:53.851 --> 14:55.311
What do you want me to do?

14:55.311 --> 14:58.731
Talk some sense into her.
Fix her.

14:58.731 --> 15:01.692
Carol, the problem is you.

15:01.692 --> 15:04.153
Excuse me?
I love my daughter.

15:04.153 --> 15:05.947
Oh, congratulations.

15:05.947 --> 15:08.616
Look, Carol, I think you need
to go to our sister program.

15:08.616 --> 15:10.618
It's for family and friends
of alcoholics.

15:10.618 --> 15:12.286
Sam's been sober
for a while now.

15:12.286 --> 15:13.663
You are the one that needs help.

15:13.663 --> 15:15.206
And Carol, put down the shears.

15:15.206 --> 15:16.624
I can hear you
stress-gardening.

15:16.624 --> 15:19.168
I swear the couch is really,
wildly comfortable.

15:19.168 --> 15:21.337
Oh, yeah, I love this couch.

15:21.337 --> 15:23.297
Oh, just, um...
Yeah, you can...

15:23.297 --> 15:24.841
-I can, uh...
-Yeah.

15:24.841 --> 15:26.717
-Yeah.
-Yeah, my parents

15:26.717 --> 15:28.302
decided to dump
all my stuff here,

15:28.302 --> 15:30.471
'cause I'm dead to them now.

15:30.471 --> 15:31.514
Right.

15:34.225 --> 15:36.185
Your mom's
always so mad at you,

15:36.185 --> 15:37.812
but this is a whole new energy
for me.

15:37.812 --> 15:39.272
Oh, yeah.
Don't worry,

15:39.272 --> 15:40.690
I'll teach you everything
you need to know.

15:40.690 --> 15:42.316
This is gonna be fun.

15:42.316 --> 15:43.609
Yeah, like old times.

15:43.609 --> 15:45.194
-(chuckles)
-Except without the puking.

15:45.194 --> 15:46.737
-Ugh.
-Mm-hmm.

15:48.322 --> 15:50.491
(sighs)

15:50.491 --> 15:52.535
You okay?

15:53.661 --> 15:55.037
I mean...

15:56.497 --> 15:58.666
...not really.

15:58.666 --> 16:00.376
But I will be, I'll be fine.

16:02.503 --> 16:04.380
You can stay here
as long as you want.

16:04.380 --> 16:07.425
Thank you. I will.

16:07.425 --> 16:08.676
Okay.

16:08.676 --> 16:10.595
♪ ♪

16:14.223 --> 16:16.267
FELICIA: If you take out
more skateboards, just, like,

16:16.267 --> 16:17.143
-put them in the garage,
all right?
-TRENT: Got it, yep.

16:17.143 --> 16:19.228
-Move, Dad.
-Okay.

16:19.228 --> 16:20.396
Here's the number
for urgent care,

16:20.396 --> 16:22.398
Poison Control,
and the pediatrician.

16:22.398 --> 16:23.441
There's Brit's number
on there, too,

16:23.441 --> 16:25.651
-in case of emergency.
-Got it.

16:25.651 --> 16:26.694
Okay, and no screen time
after 9:00.

16:26.694 --> 16:27.945
No screens.

16:27.945 --> 16:29.697
You act like
I've never babysat before.

16:29.697 --> 16:32.325
Look, we're gonna watch
three episodes of Naruto,

16:32.325 --> 16:34.118
and then we're gonna
hit the hay, okay?

16:34.118 --> 16:35.578
Okay.

16:35.578 --> 16:37.288
Just don't do anything

16:37.288 --> 16:38.581
you and I would have done, huh?

16:38.581 --> 16:40.374
I won't.

16:42.543 --> 16:45.254
-All right, I'm gonna go.
-All right.

16:45.254 --> 16:46.672
-Zacky, I love you.
-ZACK: Love you, too.

16:48.049 --> 16:50.134
NATHANIEL: All right,
how we doing, everybody?

16:50.134 --> 16:53.512
I see a few stragglers.
Not surprised.

16:53.512 --> 16:55.932
Fink, of course, late.

16:55.932 --> 16:58.434
So, listen, I have good news
from Corporate.

16:58.434 --> 17:01.562
They told me,
"We are going to double

17:01.562 --> 17:04.232
your operating budget.
You killed it."

17:04.232 --> 17:06.901
And I said, "No,
I didn't kill it, my team did."

17:06.901 --> 17:10.446
So, I want you guys to feel
so good about yourselves.

17:10.446 --> 17:13.282
Absolutely destroyed
this assignment,

17:13.282 --> 17:15.451
and I want you guys
to just go nuts

17:15.451 --> 17:16.994
and have a great time.

17:16.994 --> 17:18.579
You guys earned this,
you worked so hard...

17:18.579 --> 17:20.706
-Nathaniel...
-Yes, indeed.

17:22.124 --> 17:23.209
Uh, all right.

17:23.209 --> 17:25.795
I guess I got a raise.
Already.

17:25.795 --> 17:27.588
And trust me,
everyone is gonna be getting

17:27.588 --> 17:29.924
some really nice
Christmas bonuses,

17:29.924 --> 17:33.678
or Hannukah bonuses,
whatever your thing.

17:33.678 --> 17:36.556
Uh, all right.
This is not a raise.

17:36.556 --> 17:39.016
I actually just got served...

17:40.268 --> 17:41.519
...by my wife.

17:41.519 --> 17:43.354
Um, listen, everybody,

17:43.354 --> 17:46.232
my wife has been, um...

17:47.733 --> 17:51.571
...intercourse-ing
with a New York Yankee.

17:51.571 --> 17:54.073
But yeah, so she's been
sleeping with a Yankee,

17:54.073 --> 17:58.327
and, um, I may have to just stay
in New York for a little bit.

17:58.327 --> 17:59.662
But listen,
all great news tonight.

17:59.662 --> 18:00.913
I could be back tomorrow.

18:00.913 --> 18:03.833
None of us know
what tomorrow brings.

18:03.833 --> 18:05.751
Jeff, I gave you a column,
and maybe tomorrow it's gone,

18:05.751 --> 18:09.755
'cause you got mauled by a--
a squirrel,

18:09.755 --> 18:13.301
and it had rabies,
and you-- you're dead.

18:13.301 --> 18:15.261
Or maybe David's having
an affair like my wife was,

18:15.261 --> 18:16.804
and your wife decides
she's gonna stab you

18:16.804 --> 18:19.432
in the neck with a,
with a pen, and you're dead.

18:19.432 --> 18:20.933
Hey, maybe you should
take a walk, you know?

18:20.933 --> 18:22.768
-Just hang up and...
-Thank you, Sam, yes.

18:22.768 --> 18:24.437
I am gonna take a walk.

18:24.437 --> 18:26.522
I'll talk to you guys soon.
I'm hanging up.

18:27.648 --> 18:29.483
Oh, my God!

18:29.483 --> 18:31.110
Why, God?!

18:31.110 --> 18:35.072
Oh, no, Karen!

18:35.072 --> 18:36.782
Oh, God!

18:36.782 --> 18:38.326
(clears throat)
I'll-- I'll leave the...

18:38.326 --> 18:39.577
Goddammit...

18:40.870 --> 18:42.538
'Cause we can do it, too.
Okay.

18:42.538 --> 18:44.915
Well, that was fun.

18:44.915 --> 18:48.544
This'll be nice.
One less dish to clean.

18:48.544 --> 18:51.589
God forbid
she should wash a plate.

18:51.589 --> 18:54.592
I-I've seen her
wash plates before.

18:54.592 --> 18:56.218
Well, I have not,
and I've been living with her

18:56.218 --> 18:57.595
a lot longer than you have.

18:58.846 --> 19:01.182
Go, eat.
I'm not hungry.

19:01.182 --> 19:02.683
(drink pouring)

19:02.683 --> 19:04.185
Carol, I have to say something.

19:08.522 --> 19:09.649
You're in the wrong.

19:11.192 --> 19:12.777
Excuse me?

19:12.777 --> 19:15.655
-You're in the wrong.
-Mm, that's not possible.

19:15.655 --> 19:17.198
You never should have
read her journal.

19:18.824 --> 19:21.202
And you should apologize.

19:21.202 --> 19:24.246
I'm-- I'm sorry.
It's the truth.

19:24.246 --> 19:27.875
No, wait.
I'm not sorry.

19:27.875 --> 19:31.128
I have to stop saying "sorry"
for things I'm not sorry for.

19:31.128 --> 19:34.882
Bob, dear?
It's been a very long day.

19:34.882 --> 19:37.593
Why don't you go
restring your ukulele?

19:39.470 --> 19:40.638
BOB:
All right.

19:49.855 --> 19:51.399
Karen, what's up, baby?
It's-it's me, your Nate-Nate.

19:51.399 --> 19:52.733
I'm in Poughkeepsie, New York,

19:52.733 --> 19:54.735
on a Balance Brothers retreat.

19:54.735 --> 19:56.362
MAN:
Tell her how you feel, bro.

19:56.362 --> 19:58.572
Yeah, listen.
Baby, I'm getting, like,

19:58.572 --> 20:00.491
into a real primeval mindset.

20:00.491 --> 20:03.327
-MAN: Open up.
-I am, okay? Just...

20:03.327 --> 20:05.788
I'm just-- I want you to know
that I know

20:05.788 --> 20:07.456
that I got a lot
of work to do,

20:07.456 --> 20:09.792
and it's work
that I want to do, okay?

20:09.792 --> 20:11.252
MAN:
Yeah, why should she
believe you?

20:11.252 --> 20:13.504
'Cause I've changed.
I've changed, baby!

20:13.504 --> 20:16.590
All right?
I left Boston, I came back here.

20:16.590 --> 20:18.634
I'm gonna hunker down
with these warriors,

20:18.634 --> 20:20.344
and I'm gonna make progress,

20:20.344 --> 20:22.555
and it's gonna come
from the heart, all right?

20:22.555 --> 20:24.807
Let-let me be
your only Yankee.

20:24.807 --> 20:28.185
Let me be your Yankee, I'm gonna
bat a thousand for you.

20:28.185 --> 20:30.604
I know I hurt you.
I want to make this right.

20:30.604 --> 20:32.773
I'm gonna put rose petals
on the bed.

20:32.773 --> 20:35.443
I'm gonna make
the swan towels like you like.

20:35.443 --> 20:36.652
-All right, Nate. Wrap it up.
-What's that? Okay, yeah.

20:36.652 --> 20:38.404
So, I gotta go.

20:38.404 --> 20:40.448
That was Coach Kevin,
we're going kayaking,

20:40.448 --> 20:42.283
so I'm gonna go do that.

20:42.283 --> 20:44.452
And when I come back,
I'm gonna be a changed man.

20:44.452 --> 20:46.495
I love you.
And also, real quick,

20:46.495 --> 20:48.372
Nestor, you're (bleep) dead!

20:48.372 --> 20:49.206
I'm gonna (bleep) kill you!
